## Spawn a treehouse

Pick a branch name. Two commands:

```bash
cd {{ _repo_path }}
git worktree add treehouses/<branch> -b <branch> main
cd treehouses/<branch>
```

Claude users: `claude --worktree <branch>` from the CLI, or ask Claude to call `EnterWorktree` from inside a session. Both routes go through `.claude/hooks/worktree-create`.

## Who merges what

`treehouses/main/` is the maintainer's treehouse. Open an MR against `main`; the maintainer reviews and merges from there. Don't push to `main` from your own treehouse — the bare repo's hooks will reject it.

See [Worktree Treehouses 🌳](https://cute-devops.patterns.how/patterns/approaches/worktree-treehouses) for the full pattern.

